Gnathosoma
. Tectum with anterior margin rounded or subtriangular, sometimes almost straight, and occasionally with a few short, irregular projections (
23
), exceptionally with a narrow subtriangular projection (
24
), always with numerous denticles. Deutosternal groove with six rows of denticles, exceptionally five rows (
25
) or seven rows (
26
), usually preceded anteriorly and followed posteriorly by a smooth ridge; deutosternal rows with at least five denticles per row and usually some rows with over 10 denticles; exceptionally basal ( 6 th) row with fewer than five denticles (
27
